- 'Unresolved alerts' are those where the `resolved` column is 0;
- 'High-severity alerts' are those where the `severity` column is 'high';
- The `timestamp` column records the time when the alert was recorded.

- A drone is considered active if its status is 'active';
- Total flight time is calculated by summing the differences between the end and start times of completed flights;
- Average speed is the mean of the speed values recorded during flights;
- Average position accuracy is the mean of the accuracy values recorded for the drone's position;
- Total battery usage is the sum of the battery used during all flights;
- Total maintenance records count the number of times a drone has been maintained.

- 'Heavy load' refers to a maximum payload capacity greater than 5000 grams;
- 'Recently faced environmental challenges' means the drone has recorded an 'environmental' alert in the last 30 days;
- 'Maintain precise position data' indicates the drone's position accuracy is 1.0 or less;
- 'Descending rapidly' means the drone has a velocity in the Z direction less than -1.0.

- "Soared through multiple speed zones" refers to drones that have recorded at least two different speed ranks;
- "Encountered various alerts" means the drones have had at least one distinct alert message;
- "Peak speed" is the maximum speed recorded for the drone;
- "Diversity of their alerts" is the count of distinct alert messages;
- "Average frequency of these alerts" is the average count of alerts over time;
- "Overall active status" is the average active status, where 1 indicates active and 0 indicates inactive, with the result rounded up.

- "took to the air" refers to the number of flights a drone has completed;
- "total time spent soaring" refers to the total flight time;
- "average precision of their flight paths" refers to the average accuracy of the position data;
- "average altitude" refers to the average altitude during flights;
- "raised alarms" refers to the number of alerts generated.

- "total_distance" refers to the total distance flown by the drone in each flight;
- "average_speed" is the average speed of the drone during the flight;
- "battery_used" indicates the amount of battery consumed during the flight.

- "Soared the farthest" refers to the total distance covered by each drone model;
- "Sky as a grand stadium" is a metaphor for the environment in which drones operate;
- "Drones as athletes" is a metaphor for the drones' performance in terms of distance and speed.

- 'Speed greater than 0.8' refers to the drone's calculated speed being more than 0.8 units;
- 'Altitude below 1000' means the drone is flying at less than 1000 units of altitude;
- 'Completed flight status' indicates that the drone has finished its most recent flight.

- 'Completed missions' refer to flights where the status is 'completed';
- 'Soared' refers to the total number of flights;
- 'Glide through the air' refers to the average speed of the flights.

sql:
SELECT drone_id, MAX(speed) AS max_speed
FROM drone_speeds
GROUP BY drone_id;

SELECT COUNT(drone_id) 
FROM drones 
WHERE drone_id NOT IN (SELECT drone_id FROM maintenance_records);

SELECT AVG(vel_x) AS avg_vel_x, AVG(vel_y) AS avg_vel_y
FROM drone_velocities
WHERE drone_id = 1;

