- Active drones are those with a status of 'active';
- Speeds and maintenance records are considered from May 1, 2023, onwards;
- The query groups results by drone model and filters out models with no maintenance records.

- "Significant maintenance costs" refers to a total maintenance cost greater than 100;
- "Recent positions" refers to the latest recorded position timestamp being after April 1, 2023;
- "Few alerts" refers to the number of alerts being less than 5.

- "swift birds in the sky" refers to drones;
- "faster than a gentle breeze" refers to an average speed greater than 10;
- "during their flight on May 1, 2023" refers to the timestamp range from '2023-05-01 00:00:00' to '2023-05-02 00:00:00'.

- Active drones are those with a status of 'active';
- Completed flights are those with a status of 'completed';
- The speed ratio is calculated as the maximum speed of the drone divided by its average speed across all flights.

- Active drones are those currently in use or operational;
- Battery capacity is measured in milliampere-hours (mAh);
- Average speed is the mean speed calculated over multiple flights.

- Performance score is calculated using a weighted formula: 30% total distance, 20% average speed, 20% battery efficiency (1 / total battery used), 15% maintenance cost efficiency (1 / maintenance cost), and 15% maintenance frequency (1 / maintenance count);
- Battery efficiency is higher when the drone uses less battery for the same distance;
- Maintenance cost efficiency is higher when the drone incurs lower maintenance costs;
- Maintenance frequency is higher when the drone requires fewer maintenance sessions.

sql:
SELECT AVG(total_distance) AS overall_average_distance
FROM flight_logs
WHERE strftime('%J', start_time) >= strftime('%J', 'now') - 30;
